        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n> \n> Just to be sure you know but hardcoded certificates inside containers is forbidden.\n> You need to add them in the Helm chart\n\nPlease note that this is NOT a new certificate, but rather a change to an existing one.  Furthermore, this change is needed in Frankfurt to resolve an issue with the CDS python executor.\n\nI propose that we cherry-pick this change to Frankfurt to address this change, and then create a new Jira against Guilin to remove these certs from the py-executor docker and install them in helm instead.",
